<p>Once activated, this part of your brain sends a message through the vagus nerve to activate our parasympathetic nervous system ( The fight or flight response). </p>

<p>The size of your amygdala has been shown to correlate with your sensitivity to aspects of your environment you consider as threatening or unsafe.</p>

<p>Research has shown that mindfulness and stress reduction programmes reduce the size of the amygdala and people’s levels of anxiety in situations they previously experienced as threatening.</p>
